J	Yasmeen, H; Tan, QM; Ali, S; Ismail, H				Yasmeen, Humaira; Tan, Qingmei; Ali, Sharafat; Ismail, Hina			Managing environmental quality in Pakistan through sustainable development of energy-economy-environment (3E): insights from graph model of conflict resolution (GMCR)	MANAGEMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL QUALITY			English	Article						Environmental quality; GMCR; Energy; Economy; Sustainable development; Conflict resolution	FINANCIAL DEVELOPMENT; EMISSION-REDUCTION; CIRCULAR ECONOMY; CONSUMPTION; GROWTH; INDUSTRY; URBANIZATION; FRAMEWORK; ATTITUDE; PROMOTE	Purpose The sustainable development of the energy-economy-environment (3E) needs to ensure the balanced interplay between the energy-economy and the environment. Likewise, creating such balance has become a critical policy issue among countries worldwide. However, in the past, studies have ignored to create a balanced interplay of the energy-economy and environment. Therefore, to address said research gap, this paper aims to develop a graph model for conflict resolution (GMCR)-based strategy for the sustainable development of the 3E to ensure better environmental quality. Design/methodology/approach To develop a strategic framework for the balanced interplay between the energy-economy and the environment, the study used the GMCR approach and designed a mechanism for the sustainable development of the 3E to ensure better environmental quality in the context of Pakistan. Findings The results from the GMCR indicate that sustainable development of the 3E to ensure better environmental quality is possible when government focuses on the sustainable growth of the economy through environmental policies and the use of renewable energy. Practical implications By solving the 3E conflict, this study provides policy insights for the government of Pakistan for the sustainable development of the energy economy and the environment to ensure better environmental quality in the country. Originality/value For the first time, this paper tried to put forward a way through which conflicting objectives can be achieved together for the sustainable development of the 3E to ensure better environmental quality.	[Yasmeen, Humaira; Tan, Qingmei; Ali, Sharafat] Nanjing Univ Aeronaut & Astronaut, Coll Econ & Management, Nanjing, Peoples R China; [Ali, Sharafat] Govt Grad Coll Kot Sultan, Dept Econ, Layyah, Pakistan; [Ismail, Hina] Natl Univ Modern Languages NUML, Multan Campus, Multan, Pakistan	Ali, S (corresponding author), Nanjing Univ Aeronaut & Astronaut, Coll Econ & Management, Nanjing, Peoples R China.; Ali, S (corresponding author), Govt Grad Coll Kot Sultan, Dept Econ, Layyah, Pakistan.	humaira.yasmeen@nuaa.edu.cn; tanchangchina@sina.com; sharafat.ali.rana@gmail.com; hina.ismail@numl.edu.pk	Ali, Sharafat/G-3381-2014	Ali, Sharafat/0000-0001-7893-4055			Ahmed W, 2020, SYMMETRY-BASEL, V12, DOI 10.3390/sym12081203; Ali S., 2019, QUAL QUANT, V53, P561, DOI [10.1007/s11135-018-0775-9, DOI 10.1007/S11135-018-0775-9]; Ali S, 2021, ENVIRON DEV SUSTAIN, V23, P11881, DOI 10.1007/s10668-020-01147-5; Ali S, 2020, ENVIRON DEV SUSTAIN, V22, P3839, DOI 10.1007/s10668-019-00365-w; Ali S, 2019, J SYST SCI SYST ENG, V28, P356, DOI 10.1007/s11518-019-5413-0; Ameer A, 2020, MANAG ENVIRON QUAL; Anwar J, 2016, RENEW SUST ENERG REV, V65, P1065, DOI 10.1016/j.rser.2016.07.037; Armeanu DS, 2017, ENERGIES, V10, DOI 10.3390/en10030381; Bhattacharya S., 2007, ENV WORKING PAPER SE, V113; Bridge G, 2013, ENERG POLICY, V53, P331, DOI 10.1016/j.enpol.2012.10.066; Cai W, 2019, SCI TOTAL ENVIRON, V665, P23, DOI 10.1016/j.scitotenv.2019.02.069; Cheema AR, 2015, NATURE, V524, P35, DOI 10.1038/524035e; Chen TL, 2019, J CLEAN PROD, V239, DOI 10.1016/j.jclepro.2019.117860; Foxon TJ, 2011, ECOL ECON, V70, P2258, DOI 10.1016/j.ecolecon.2011.07.014; Geng CX, 2020, ENERG POLICY, V137, DOI 10.1016/j.enpol.2019.111081; Guo XF, 2017, J CLEAN PROD, V140, P1313, DOI 10.1016/j.jclepro.2016.10.021; Harijan K, 2011, ENERGY, V36, P6068, DOI 10.1016/j.ene