J	Rego, LC; Vieira, GIA				Rego, Leandro Chaves; Vieira, Giannini Italino Alves			A Note on Policy Equilibrium and Generalized Metarationalities for Multiple Decision-Maker Conflicts	IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON SYSTEMS MAN CYBERNETICS-SYSTEMS			English	Article						Stability criteria; Cybernetics; Indexes; Terrorism; Games; Conflict; generalized metarationalities; graph model; stability notions	GRAPH MODEL	We present three problems found in this paper "Policy equilibrium and generalized metarationalities for multiple decision-maker conflicts," by Zeng et al., published in IEEE Trans. Syst., Man, Cybern. A, Syst., Humans, vol. 37, no. 4, pp. 456-463, Jul. 2007. More specifically, we show by means of counterexamples that: 1) the definition proposed for n-decision maker (DM) conflicts does not coincide with the existing generalized metarationality defined by these same authors for conflicts with 2 DMs; 2) the equivalence between generalized metarationality for 2 rounds and symmetric metarational stability is false; and 3) generalized metarational equilibrium does not imply policy equilibrium.	[Rego, Leandro Chaves] Univ Fed Ceara, Stat & Appl Math Dept, BR-60455760 Fortaleza, Ceara, Brazil; [Rego, Leandro Chaves] Univ Fed Pernambuco, Grad Program Stat & Management Engn, Recife, PE, Brazil; [Vieira, Giannini Italino Alves] Univ Fed Ceara, Crateus Campus, BR-63700000 Crateus, Brazil; [Vieira, Giannini Italino Alves] Univ Fed Ceara, Grad Program Modeling & Quantitat Methods, Fortaleza, Ceara, Brazil	Rego, LC (corresponding author), Univ Fed Ceara, Stat & Appl Math Dept, BR-60455760 Fortaleza, Ceara, Brazil.	leandro@dema.ufc.br; italino@ufc.br	Rego, Leandro Chaves/E-6286-2013; Vieira, Giannini/X-2822-2019	Rego, Leandro Chaves/0000-0002-4091-024X; 	Conselho Nacional de Desenvolvimento Cientifico e TecnologicoConselho Nacional de Desenvolvimento Cientifico e Tecnologico (CNPQ) [308522/2013-3, 307556/2017-4]	The work of L. C. Rego was supported by the Conselho Nacional de Desenvolvi