J	Walker, SB; hipel, keith william; Inohara, T				walker, sean g. bernath; hipel, keith william; Inohara, Takehiro			Strategic decision making for improved environmental security: Coalitions and attitudes	JOURNAL OF SYSTEMS SCIENCE AND SYSTEMS ENGINEERING			English	Article						Graph model for conflict resolution; attitudes; coalitions; COAT; decision support system; conflict		The utilization of decision support systems which are flexible enough to handle information about cooperative behavior and stakeholder attitudes are useful for analyzing complex social conflicts. One such conflict which arose from the redevelopment of a private brownfield property in Kitchener, Ontario, Canada is examined using such a decision support tool. Specifically, a formal model referred to as COAT which allows for the examination of conflicts with both coalition and attitude properties is rigorously defined and then implemented within the framework of the Graph Model for Conflict Resolution in order that insights may be gained on how the decision makers can reach win-win resolutions.	[walker, sean g. bernath; hipel, keith william] Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Conflict Anal Grp, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada; [Inohara, Takehiro] Tokyo Inst Technol, Dept Decis & Value Sci, Tokyo 152, Japan	Walker, SB (corresponding author), Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Conflict Anal Grp, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada.	sgwalker@uwaterloo.ca; kwhipel@uwaterloo.ca; inohara.t.aa@m.titech.ac.jp	Inohara, Takehiro/ABG-3842-2020; Inohara, Takehiro/B-9298-2015	Inohara, Takehiro/0000-0003-4981-0904	Centre for International Governance Innovation, Waterloo, Ontario, Canada; Natural Science and Engineering Research Council of CanadaNatural Sciences and Engineering Research Council of Canada (NSERC); Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology (MEXT) in JapanMinistry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology, Japan (MEXT); Japan Society for the Promotion of Science (JSPS)