J	kilgour, d. marc; Fang, Liping; hipel, keith william				kilgour, d. marc; Fang, Liping; hipel, keith william			Negotiation support using the decision support system GMCR	GROUP DECISION AND NEGOTIATION			English	Article; Proceedings Paper	Session on Negotiation Processes - Modeling Frameworks and Information Technology, at the TIMS/ORSA Boston Meeting	APR 24-27, 1994	BOSTON, MA	INFORMS, Sect Grp Decis & Negotiat		conflict resolution; decision support system; environmental conflict; graph model; negotiation support; negotiations	EQUILIBRIA; CONFLICTS; GAMES	The Graph Model for Conflict Resolution constitutes a unique and flexible approach to the representation, analysis, and understanding of strategic conflict. This methodology, as implemented in the Decision Support System GMCR, constitutes a useful tool for negotiation support. Because GMCR includes efficient algorithms for calculating the stability of states, it encourages extensive comparisons of the consequences of different models of negotiators' decision making. GMCR also facilitates modifications to the way in which the conflict is represented, encouraging sensitivity and what-if analyses. The applicability of GMCR to negotiations is discussed in general, and in the context of a specific case study in environmental conflict resolution.	UNIV WATERLOO,DEPT SYST DESIGN ENGN,WATERLOO,ON N2L 3G1,CANADA; RYERSON POLYTECH INST,DEPT MECH ENGN,TORONTO,ON M5B 2K3,CANADA; DEPT STAT & ACTUARIAL SCI,WATERLOO,ON,CANADA	kilgour, d. marc (corresponding author), WILFRID LAURIER UNIV,DEPT MATH,WATERLOO,ON N2L 3C5,CANADA.						BERGMANNBAKER U, 1991, THESIS U SAARLANDES; Brams S, 1993, THEORY MOVES; BRAMS SJ, 1981, CONFLICT MANAG PEACE, V6, P39, DOI 10.1177/073889428100600103; BURTT B, 1991, KITCHENER WATER 1102; BURTT B, 1993, KITCHENER WATER 0313; CROWLEY K, 1991, KITCHENER WATER 1009; CROWLEY K, 1991, KITCHENER WATER 1008, pA1; Fang L., 1993, INTERACTIVE DECISION; FANG LP, 1989, EUR J OPER RES, V41, P86, DOI 10.1016/0377-221