J	Garcia, A; obeidi, amer; hipel, keith william				garcia, amanda; obeidi, amer; hipel, keith william			Initial state stability for n-decision-maker conflicts	INFOR			English	Article						Graph Model for conflict resolution; solution concepts; decision-making	GRAPH MODEL; GENERALIZED METARATIONALITIES; STRATEGIC ANALYSIS; FUZZY PREFERENCES; RESOLUTION	A new family of stability concepts, initial state stabilities, are introduced to complement existing solutions concepts within the Graph Model framework. These novel stability concepts address both risk-averse and risk-seeking decision-makers by comparing the consequences of moving from a given starting state to those of remaining in that state. Initial state stabilities are defined and introduced using a simple example. Their relationships with both metarational and standard Graph Model solutions concepts are explored.	[garcia, amanda; obeidi, amer; hipel, keith william] Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Waterloo, ON, Canada; [obeidi, amer] Univ Waterloo, Dept Management Sci, Waterloo, ON, Canada	Garcia, A (corresponding author), Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Waterloo, ON, Canada.	a9garcia@uwaterloo.ca			Natural Science and Engineering Research Council of CanadaNatural Sciences and Engineering Research Council of Canada (NSERC)	The authors acknowledge the financial support of the Natural Science and Engineering Research Council of Canada.	Abul Bashar M, 2012, IEEE T FUZZY SYST, V20, P760, DOI 10.1109/TFUZZ.2012.2183603; Bashar MA, 2016, IEEE T FUZZY SYST, V24, P765, DOI 10.1109/TFUZZ.2015.2446536; Fang L., 1993, INTERACTIVE DECISION; Fraser N.M., 1984, CONFLICT ANAL MODELS; FRASER NM, 1979, IEEE T SYST MAN CYB, V9, P805, DOI 10.1109/TSMC.1979.4310131; Garcia A, 2016, ENERG POLICY, V91, P397, DOI 10.1016/j.enpol.2016.01.033; Hamouda L, 2006, APPL MATH COMPUT, V179, P314, DOI 10.1016/j.amc.2005.11.109; He S, 2016, EUR J OPER RES, V51, P103; He SW, 2017, EUR J OPER RES, V257, P919, DOI 10.1016/j.ejor.2016.08.