J	li, kevin w.; kilgour, d. marc; hipel, keith william				li, kevin w.; kilgour, d. marc; hipel, keith william			Status quo analysis of the Flathead River conflict	WATER RESOURCES RESEARCH			English	Article						conflict analysis; graph model for conflict resolution; status quo analysis; water resources conflict	DECISION-SUPPORT-SYSTEM; EQUILIBRIA; MODEL; GAMES; WATER	Status quo analysis algorithms developed within the paradigm of the graph model for conflict resolution are applied to an international river basin conflict involving the United States and Canada to assess the likeliness of various compromise resolutions. The conflict arose because the state of Montana feared that further expansion of the Sage Creek Coal Company facilities in Canada would pollute the Flathead River, which flows from British Columbia to Montana. Significant insights not generally available from a static stability analysis are obtained about potential resolutions of the conflict under study and about how decision makers' interactions may direct the conflict to distinct resolutions. Analyses also show how political considerations may affect a particular decision maker's choice, thereby influencing the evolution of the conflict.	Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada; Wilfrid Laurier Univ, Dept Math, Waterloo, ON N2L 3C5, Canada	li, kevin w. (corresponding author), Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada.	w8li@engmail.uwaterloo.ca; mkilgour@wlu.ca; kwhipel@uwaterloo.ca	Li, Kevin/A-4272-2008	Li, Kevin/0000-0001-7756-9797			BENNETT PG, 1980, FUTURES, V12, P489, DOI 10.1016/0016-3287(80)90005-1; Brams S.J, 1994, THEORY OF MOVES; BRAMS SJ, 1981, CONFLICT MANAG PEACE, V6, P39, DOI 10.1177/073889428100600103; CONCA K, 2003, ENV PEACEKEEPING; Dimitrov RS, 2002, SOC NATUR RESOUR, V15, P677, DOI 10.1080/08941920290069281; Fang L., 1993, INTERACTIVE DECISION; FANG L, 1989, EUR J OPER RES, V41, P80; Fang LP, 2003, IEEE T SYST MAN CY C, V33, P42, 