J	Bristow, M; Fang, Liping; hipel, keith william				Bristow, Michele; Fang, Liping; hipel, keith william			Agent-Based Modeling of Competitive and Cooperative Behavior Under Conflict	IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON SYSTEMS MAN CYBERNETICS-SYSTEMS			English	Article						Agent-based modeling; graph model for conflict resolution; policy simulation; tragedy of the commons	DECISION-SUPPORT-SYSTEM; COLLECTIVE ACTION; GROUP-SIZE; EQUILIBRIA; PREFERENCE; TRAGEDY; GAMES	A novel agent-based framework for modeling and simulating competitive and cooperative behavior under conflict is proposed. Formal definitions of Nash, general metarational, symmetric metarational, and sequential stability decision rules reflecting human behavior under conflict are presented in this paper. The definitions are inspired by the solution concepts of the graph model for conflict resolution and are conceived for implantation in the proposed agent-based modeling and simulation framework. With these decision rules, competitive and cooperative conflict dynamics are simulated for a theoretical common-pool resources dilemma. Moreover, policies can be tested for their effectiveness in avoiding or recouping from a tragedy of the commons.	[Bristow, Michele; hipel, keith william] Univ Waterloo, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada; [Fang, Liping] Ryerson Univ, Dept Mech & Ind Engn, Toronto, ON M5B 2K3, Canada	Bristow, M (corresponding author), Univ Waterloo, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada.	mtheng@uwaterloo.ca; lfang@ryerson.ca; kwhipel@uwaterloo.ca					Abul Bashar M, 2012, IEEE T FUZZY SYST, V20, P760, DOI 10.1109/TFUZZ.2012.2183603; Agrawal A, 2001, COMP POLIT STUD, V34, P63, DOI 10.1177/0010414001034001003; Axelrod R, 1997, COMPLEXITY COOPERATI; Braha D., 2006, COMPLEX ENG SYSTEMS; BRAMS SJ, 1981, CONFLICT MANAG PEACE, V6, P39, DOI 10.1177/073889428100600103; Bristow M., 2012, P GROUP DECISION NEG, P234; Bristow M, 2012, IEEE SYS MAN CYBERN, P2418, DOI 10.1109/ICSMC.2012.6378105; Bristow M, 2012, RISK ANAL, V32, P1935, DOI 10.