J	Zhu, ZM; kilgour, d. marc; hipel, keith william				Zhu, Ziming; Kilgour, D. Marc; hipel, keith william			A New Approach to Coalition Analysis Within the Graph Model	IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON SYSTEMS MAN CYBERNETICS-SYSTEMS			English	Article						Stability analysis; Oils; Analytical models; Game theory; Cybernetics; System analysis and design; Marine vehicles; Graph model; offshore oil exploration dispute; Pareto coalition analysis; strategic analysis	DECISION-SUPPORT-SYSTEM; CONFLICT-RESOLUTION; EQUILIBRIA; STABILITY	Within the framework of the graph model for conflict resolution, the concept of coalition improvement is generalized, resulting in new definitions of Nash, general metarational, symmetric metarational, and sequential stability applicable to coalitions. To illustrate how these generalized stability definitions can be applied to a real conflict, they are used to analyze an offshore oil exploration dispute that occurred in the South China Sea in 2014. The novel approach reveals which coalitions can upset a noncooperative equilibrium or support new cooperative equilibria, and which decision makers can benefit from joining a coalition.	[Zhu, Ziming] Tsinghua Univ, Res Ctr Contemporary Management, Beijing 100084, Peoples R China; [Zhu, Ziming; Kilgour, D. Marc; hipel, keith william] Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada; [Kilgour, D. Marc] Wilfrid Laurier Univ, Dept Math, Waterloo, ON N2L 3C5, Canada; [hipel, keith william] Ctr Int Governance Innovat, Waterloo, ON N2L 6C2, Canada; [hipel, keith william] Balsillie Sch Int Affairs, Waterloo, ON N2L 6C2, Canada	Zhu, ZM (corresponding author), Tsinghua Univ, Res Ctr Contemporary Management, Beijing 100084, Peoples R China.	zhuzm.08@sem.tsinghua.edu.cn			China Scholarship [201503170062]	This work was supported by China Scholarship under Grant 201503170062. This paper was recommended by Associate Editor P. Guo.	[Anonymous], ECONOMIST; [Anonymous], GUARDIAN; BRAMS SJ, 1981, CONFLICT MANAG P