J	Philpot, SL; Johnson, PA; hipel, keith william				Philpot, Simone L.; Johnson, Peter A.; hipel, keith william			Analysis of a brownfield management conflict in Canada	HYDROLOGICAL RESEARCH LETTERS			English	Article						graph model; conflict analysis; water resources; brownfields	DECISION-SUPPORT-SYSTEM; GRAPH MODEL; COALITION ANALYSIS; PART	A strategic analysis of an ongoing brownfield management conflict in Elmira, Ontario, Canada is conducted using the Graph Model for Conflict Resolution. This investigation of the situation as it existed in late 2016 constitutes an expansion of an earlier analysis of the dispute which focused on cleansing the groundwater aquifer, polluted by a chemical company in Elmira, to a controversy over the management of the pollution impacts on an adjacent creek. Besides the chemical plant, the other decision-makers involved in the 2016 dispute are the Ministry of Environment and Climate Change of the Province of Ontario, local government, and a citizens' advisory group. The connections of the 2016 conflict to the earlier study which took place in 1991 are discussed and the evolution of the previous situation to the current one is explored in depth, along with strategic insights.	[Philpot, Simone L.; Johnson, Peter A.] Univ Waterloo, Dept Geog & Environm Management, Waterloo, ON, Canada; [hipel, keith william] Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Waterloo, ON, Canada; [hipel, keith william] Ctr Int Governance Innovat, Waterloo, ON, Canada; [hipel, keith william] Balsillie Sch Int Affairs, Waterloo, ON, Canada	Philpot, SL (corresponding author), Univ Waterloo, 200 Univ Ave W, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada.	sphilpot@uwaterloo.ca	philpot, simone l./AAN-1331-2020	johnson, peter a./0000-0003-4572-2915			Abul Bashar M, 2012, IEEE T FUZZY SYST, V20, P760, DOI 10.1109/TFUZZ.2012.2183603; Baetz MC, 1998, CAN PUBLIC ADMIN, V41, P395, DOI 10.1111/j.1754-7121.1998.tb01295.x; Bashar MA, 2014, FUZZY SET SYST, V246, P34, DOI 10.1016/j.fss.2014.02.011; 