J	hipel, keith william; kilgour, d. marc; Fang, Liping; peng, xyj				hipel, keith william; kilgour, d. marc; Fang, Liping; peng, xyj			Strategic decision support for the services industry	IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON ENGINEERING MANAGEMENT			English	Article						conflict resolution; decision making; negotiation support; service tool	SYSTEM GMCR	The graph model for conflict resolution and the associated decision support system GMCR II are presented as a comprehensive service tool that can provide strategic advice to leaders and managers, in industry, government, and other organizations, who must ensure the success of their enterprises within an increasingly competitive environment on a local, national, or international level. In addition to furnishing an overview of the graph model and the design of GMCR II, this paper describes general situations in which advisors providing a decision support service may use this unique computerized technology. An international trade dispute is utilized to illustrate how GMCR II can be applied to study real-world interactive decision making systematically and effectively.	Wilfrid Laurier Univ, Dept Math, Waterloo, ON N2L 3C5, Canada; Univ Waterloo, Dept Syst Design Engn, Waterloo, ON N2L 3G1, Canada; Ryerson Polytech Univ, Dept Mech Aerosp & Ind Engn, Toronto, ON M5B 2K3, Canada; SWI Systemware Inc, Toronto, ON M4P 1E4, Canada	hipel, keith william (corresponding author), Wilfrid Laurier Univ, Dept Math, Waterloo, ON N2L 3C5, Canada.						ARROW KJ, 1986, SOCIAL CHOICE MULTIP; Chankong V., 1983, MULTIOBJECTIVE DECIS; Checkland P., 1990, SOFT SYSTEMS METHODO; Fang L., 1993, INTERACTIVE DECISION; FANG L, 1997, P 1997 IEEE INT C SY, V1, P341; Fisher R., 1991, GETTING YES NEGOTIAT; FRASER NM, 1987, P IMACS IFOR 1 INT C; Hipel KW, 1997, APPL MATH COMPUT, V83, P117, DOI 10.1016/S0096-3003(96)00170-1; HIPEL KW, 1990, EUR J OPER RES, V46, P235, DOI 10.1016/0377-2217(90)90134-W; HOBBS BF, 1986, IEEE T SYST MAN CYB, V16, P384, DOI 10.1109/TSMC.1986.430